INSERT INTO reviews VALUE('Russell Moss',4,2,2,'Overall a very interesting class. Couldn''t take it in person with actual wine tasting, but professors recommended a bunch of wines we could taste to go along with the material, and students were encouraged to drink tea, coffee, or juices if they couldn''t acquire wines. Class is more about the process of making wines and growing grapes, compared to the hotel wines class. COVID semester consisted of module quizzes and small activities. Optional papers could bring you to a 110\%%, so it is pretty easy to get an A/A+.','VIEN 1104',1306);
