INSERT INTO reviews VALUE('Kathy Arnink',5,1,1,'The class is very interesting and you learn about the types of wines, but a lot about vineyard management and the growing of the grapes. You learn that there is so much more than you thought to managing a vineyard, and that so many small subtle things go into making a perfect bottle. Weekly quizzes, and 3 wine review papers that require at least 1 journal. Super easy and not a lot of time required for this class. 10 extra credit points total, so you can get up to 110. Arnink is a very nice professor, and Russ is very nice and entertaining, and has a lot to share about his expertise in vineyard management. Do not take ECE 2300 after or you will fall asleep during it.','VIEN 1104',1306);
