INSERT INTO reviews VALUE('Lillian Lee',5,3,4,'Took in Spring 2018. Took this class as a first-time coder. The assignments were more NLP oriented our semester and were pretty easy. Workload consisted of around 5-6 assignments and weekly labs. Prelims were pretty fair. DO THE PRACTICE PRELIMS AND REVIEW LABS!! I absolutely loved Bracy''s powerpoints. The color coding, the diagrams, and the flow of call frames were all used so well. The consultants and TAs were also very helpful! Note: Consulting hours can get wild close to deadlines so get started on assignments asap and ask consultants all your conceptual questions during lab.','CS 1110',347);
